theorem Topology.closure_interior_closure_eq_closure_interior_of_P1
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hP1 : Topology.P1 A) :
    closure (interior (closure A)) = closure (interior A) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  ·
    -- First, show `interior (closure A) ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
    have h₁ : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
      -- `interior (closure A)` is contained in `closure A`.
      have h_int_cl : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
      -- From `P1`, we have `A ⊆ closure (interior A)`. Taking closures yields
      -- `closure A ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
      have h_cl : closure A ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
        have : closure A ⊆ closure (closure (interior A)) :=
          closure_mono (hP1 : A ⊆ closure (interior A))
        simpa [closure_closure] using this
      exact Set.Subset.trans h_int_cl h_cl
    -- Taking closures preserves inclusions.
    exact closure_mono h₁
  ·
    -- Conversely, `interior A ⊆ interior (closure A)` by monotonicity.
    have h₂ : interior A ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
      apply interior_mono
      exact subset_closure
    -- Taking closures yields the desired inclusion.
    exact closure_mono h₂

theorem Topology.P2_closure_idempotent {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P2 (closure (closure A)) ↔ Topology.P2 (closure A) := by
  have h_eq : closure (closure A) = closure A := by
    simpa [closure_closure]
  simpa [h_eq]
